SIMPLE: hermetically
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hermetically
<hw>Her*met"ic*al*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In an
hermetical manner; chemically.</def> <rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>By fusion, so as to form an air-tight
closure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ A vessel or tube is <xex>hermetically</xex> sealed when
it is closed completely against the passage of air or other fluid by
fusing the extremity; -- sometimes less properly applied to any
air-tight closure.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hermit</ent>⟦br⟧
